825-493a-9d67-df375ee1d834","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Zoom Telephonics provides a five-year warranty and technical support by email on weekdays during US EDT business hours. The vendor requires a $15 handling fee to be included with any modem sent in for repair under warranty. The Zoom Telephonics support page is well organized with useful resources such as Frequently Asked Questions, warranty information, firmware, drivers and manuals."]},"id":"8bef4f6b-d645-45ad-be74-2087939b2343","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"f86816a0-cb55-4583-b8fe-5b469a44809e","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["In a market crowded with commodity-level DOCSIS 2.0 cable modems competing for attention, one of the ways in which Zoom Telephonics distinguishes itself is through product design considerations that reflect a corporate awareness of industrial impact on the ecology of the Earth. The Zoom External Cable Modem 5241 has an ENERGY STAR-qualified power adapter. Furthermore, Zoom Telephonics is committed to conforming to Europe’s Restriction on Use of Hazardous Substances (RoHS), which regulates the amounts of poisonous substances (such as lead and mercury) that products can contain.","The Zoom External Cable Modem 5241 conforms to DOCSIS 2.0, which means that it is nearing the end of its useful product life cycle as more cable operators update their cable modem termination systems to support DOCSIS 3.0. At the current rate of ISP DOCSIS 3.0 adoption, if you purchase this cable modem, you will probably wind up getting a DOCSIS 3.0-certified cable modem before Zoom’s five-year warranty expires."]},"id":"578f3e1f-63cf-457f-a41b-804dc78f24c6","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_49452","url":"/zoom-external-5241-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"rebecca-armstrong","url":"/author/rebecca-armstrong","dateCreated":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","name":"Rebecca Armstrong","dateModified":"2019-04-17T20:46:58Z","id":"6pCy2z6qSDBXrw3J9gsMqa",